cs.LG, cs.MA, cs.AI, cs.NI, cs.SI

The paper proposes an algorithm that leverages multi-agent reinforcement learning to optimize the sensing policy of mobile users participating in mobile crowdsensing tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with the interaction of mobile users with their sensing environment, which suggests the sub-categories cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as possible choices.
